question: The Doberai Peninsula is in this nation's easternmost province, and the city of Pontianak in its province of West Kalimantan lies on an island shared by two other countries. The Lombok and Sunda Straits are major shipping lanes in the south of this country, and Bali is a major resort island here. Including the islands of Sumatra and Java name this primarily Muslim archipelagic nation with capital Jakarta.

In August 2024, a US federal court ruled that this tech giant illegally maintained a monopoly and engaged in anti-competitive practices to suppress rivals. The case was brought by the Department of Justice, which argued that the company's dominance stifled innovation and harmed consumers. The case involved this company's rumored mutl-billion dollar payments to Apple and other tech companies to be the default search engine on their devices/platforms. Which tech giant is this?

One of these animals named Elsey tells Maureen that "in Cyberland we only drink Diet Coke" in the musical RENT. In an Irish myth, Cuchulainn is unable to prevent one of these animals from being stolen in a famous "raid of Cooley." In Into the Woods, one of these named Milky White is Jack's only friend. A "pox" of these animals was the source of the first vaccines. Name this common bovine animal which chews its cud and produces milk.

This artist's iconic music video for "Thriller," directed by John Landis and released in 1983, revolutionized the music industry with its elaborate choreography, special effects, and cinematic storytelling. The video, which runs for over 13 minutes, features a zombie dance sequence that has become a cultural phenomenon, and its album of the same name remains the best-selling album of all time. Who is this artist, also known for his signature moonwalk dance move and chart-topping hits like "Billie Jean" and "Beat It"?

The remains of a leader of this movement, Martin Bucer, were burned by Mary I ["the first"]. The Marburg Colloquy was called to resolve a dispute between Huldrych Zwingli and another leader of this movement. The Council of Trent codified the "Counter-" response to this movement, whose early proponents criticized the sale of indulgences. This movement started on All Saints' Day, 1517, when Martin Luther posted his 95 Theses in Wittenberg. Name this historical period in which Christian churches broke away from the Roman Catholic Church.

The would-be assassin of this person clashed with his attorney, Judy Clarke, when told his target survived. She received a standing ovation from Congress when she appeared to cast a vote in August 2011. Less than 7 months earlier, she was fighting for her life, after being shot in the head by Jared Loughner in a Safeway parking lot. Name this Arizona congresswoman who resigned her office in January 2012.

In AC circuits, this quantity's namesake right triangle can be used to find its "apparent" form. Intensity is equal to this quantity over area. In an electrical circuit, this quantity can be expressed as voltage squared over resistance, though it is more commonly denoted as current squared time resistance or current times voltage. Name this physical quantity, the amount of work done per unit time, measured in Watts.

This team's iconic orange and black colors, adopted in 1947, were inspired by the owner Horace Stoneham's love of hunting and fishing. They hold the record for the most National League pennants, with 23, and have played in 20 World Series. Their home stadium, Oracle Park, boasts stunning views of the San Francisco Bay and is known for its signature splash hits into McCovey Cove. Which team, originally based in New York, moved to San Francisco in 1958 and has won eight World Series championships?
